\f0\fs24 \cf0 # Auto Video Editor\
\
Automatically adds AI-generated captions to videos uploaded to Google Drive.\
\
## Quick Start\
\
1. **Install dependencies:**\
   ```bash\
   pip install -r requirements.txt\
   ```\
\
2. **Set up Google Drive API:**\
   - Create project in [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com)\
   - Enable Google Drive API\
   - Download credentials as `credentials.json`\
\
3. **Configure environment:**\
   ```bash\
   cp .env.template .env\
   # Edit .env with your folder IDs and settings\
   ```\
\
4. **Run:**\
   ```bash\
   python src/main.py\
   ```\
\
## What it does\
\
- Monitors Google Drive folder for new videos\
- Downloads and processes videos automatically\
- Generates captions using OpenAI Whisper\
- Adds captions to videos with styling\
- Uploads finished videos to destination folder\
\
## Requirements\
\
- Python 3.8+\
- Google Drive API credentials\
- OpenAI API key (for captions)\
- 2GB+ disk space for processing\
\
## Files\
\
- `src/main.py` - Entry point\
- `src/config.py` - Settings\
- `src/services/` - Core processing logic\
- `credentials.json` - Google API credentials\
- `.env` - Configuration variables\
\
## Logs\
\
Check `logs/video_processor.log` for processing status and errors.}